determine extraction aperture

As shown in the screenshot, a circle with radius of 4.5 pixels is able to encompass most of the star's light.
Extraction aperture = 2 * radius of circle

--------------

determine_reference_stars

x axis = number of objects
y axis = count values of an individual object
The blue dot indicates our target.
10 reference stars are chosen based on its closeness (in terms of count values) with respect to our target
